Intuition
I observed that 4Sum can be reduced similarly to 3Sum. Instead of directly finding 4 numbers, I can fix two numbers and then solve the remaining problem using the two-pointer technique.

Approach
step 1 . i sorted the array just like 3 pointer , iterate i over the array
, made an empty list result
step 2 . loop condition for i in range(n-3)
define j as j = i+1
skip duplicate i
step 3 .
loop condition for j (i+1, n-2): #very important
skip duplicate j

                left pointer
                right pointer

                “after fixing i and j, reduce the problem to 2Sum using two pointers”

                define total
                compare total and target 
                define all the conditions for comparison of target and total
Complexity
Time complexity:
O(n^3)
Space complexity:
O(1)
Code
class Solution:
    def fourSum(self, nums: List[int], target: int) -> List[List[int]]:
        nums.sort()
        i = 0
        n =len(nums)
        result = []

        for i in range(n-3):
            j = i + 1
            if i > 0 and nums[i] == nums[i-1]:
                continue
            for j in range(i + 1, n - 2):
                if j > i+1 and nums[j] == nums[j-1]:
                    continue
 
                left = j + 1
                right = n - 1 
              
                while left < right:
                    total = nums[i] + nums[j] + nums[left] + nums[right]
                    if total == target:
                        result.append([nums[i] , nums[j] , nums[left] , nums[right]])
                        left += 1
                        right -= 1

                        while left < right and nums[left] == nums[left-1]:
                            left += 1

                        while left < right and nums[right] == nums[right+1]:
                            right -= 1        

                    elif total < target:
                        left += 1
                    else: 
                        right -= 1
                    
        return result
